 philosophy of language. This series explores issues of mental representation, linguistic structure and representation, and their interplay. The research presented in this series is grounded in the idea explored in the Collaborative Research Center 'The structure of representations in language, cognition and science' (SFB 991) that there is a universal format for the representation of linguistic and cognitive concepts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Feb 2021) 4aconceptual semantics. 4adynamic frame theory. 4aformal semantics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / General.2bisacsh  aAlex Dainiak.  aAntje Roßdeutscher.  aBRIDGE Workshop.  aCollaborative Research Center.  aDependency.  aDie Struktur von Repräsentationen in Sprache, Kognition und Wissenschaft.  aE. Allyn Smith.  aGerhard Schurz.  aGricean Perspective.  aHana Filip.  aHeinrich-Heine-Universität Düsseldorf.  aHenk Zeevat.  aKinds.  aLaura Kallmeyer.  aLive Meanings.  aLotte Hogeweg.  aLouise McNally.  aMartin Stokhof.  aMeaning in Use.  aMichiel van Lambalgen.  aNatalia Zevakhina.  aPaul Dekker.  aPeter Indefrey.  aRalf Naumann.  aRobert D. Van Valin, Jr.  aSFB 991.  aSander Lestrade.  aScott Grimm.  aSebastian Löbner.  aSonderforschungsbereich 991.  aThe structure of representations in language, cognition and science.  aTillmann Pross.  aconceptual closeness.  aconceptual semantics.  acorpus-based approach.  adynamic frame theory.  aformal semantics.  aframe theory.  alexicon.  alinguistic representation.  alinguistic structure.  amental representation.  aoverspecification.  asemantic constraint.1 